Package main.java

Class Customer

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.java.Customer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FrequentCustomer, RegularCustomer
    abstract class Customer
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Class that represents a default Customer, this class extends into different types of Customers. We need more than one type of Customer since the transport value is calculated differently.
    Author:
    Eduardo Nunes

    • Constructor Detail

      • Customer

        protected Customer​(java.lang.String name,
                   java.lang.String address,
                   java.lang.String email,
                   java.lang.String phoneNumber,
                   Date dateOfBirth)
            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                   java.lang.NumberFormatException
        Constructor of the class Customer, it initializes the customer's name, address, email, phone number, date of birth and orders. It is protected since it is only used by the subclasses and the registration of new customers is not implemented.
        Parameters:
        name - The customer's name.
        address - The customer's address.
        email - The customer's email.
        phoneNumber - The customer's phone number.
        dateOfBirth - The customer's date of birth.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the customer's email is invalid.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the customer's phone number is invalid.
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - if the customer's phone number is not a real phone number.
